		" 
			>
			<div></div><p>The problem about the backups is the shere amount of data that'll be needed to be backed up. The safest way would be a complete backup of all characters, not only eqplayers type data, but also stuff like active buffs, timers, lockouts etc, for every one of te ~5mil characters on record. The sensible way would be version checking to see if the data had changed from the last backup, but then again, if we trusted SoE's version checking, we wouldn't have half the patch problems we do.</p><p></p><p>Obviously backups are done at some point, I was just wondering about the practicalities.</p>	
