			>
			<br><blockquote><hr>Singinn wrote:<br><div></div><br><blockquote><hr>Idiin_Duet wrote:<br><div></div><div>The 3 hour down time while they are patching would probably be enough time to back up all the player data to the point at which the servers were taken down. </div><div> </div><div>We image and backup our main server (about 800-850 gigs) to a terabyte tape and it takes about 3 hours to do. We also do a three times a week backup to an external drive which takes far less than 3 hours to do. We have a disaster recovery plan for ALL of our servers. Why doesn't Sony?</div><div> </div><div>What they did was unacceptable. The servers should have been taken down immedately (even if they didn't have a backup of the player data) and fixed the problem then. Letting the servers remain up, letting the tainted items get dispersed and then doing selective rollbacks after HOURS have past was not the proper thing to do because it affected a lot more people than it should have. I talked to 3 people who bought stuff from the vendors. Only one so far has been rolled back as of late last night.</div><br><hr></blockquote>I know there are thousands of players anyone have an idea how much data a player may contain? I am guessing but I really don't think its all that much and by what I have heard in the past your player data is saved  every time you make a Bank or Vendor transaction, Player trade ect. Giving say 1k of raw data per Character and 500,000 Character per server. That comes out to 500meg of player data per server. A DLT tape transfers at about 3gb per min, so a Character backup may take 5-10 min for all the servers if not less<br><br><hr></blockquote><br><br><br>Then factor in game state information, flags, lockout timers, guild banks, etc.... and 1k of raw data is way too small. <br><br>Just think inventory alone, a character has: <br><br>22 equipable slots, each one with possilbly 4 items in them ( 1 item + 3 augs)<br>8 inventory slots with max 10 slot bags there, so 8 + 320 items there.<br>16 inventory slots with max 10 slot bags there, so 16 + 640 items there<br>2 shared slots with max 10 slot bags, so 2 + 80 items there.<br>1 overflow slot in case you died/left with something on your cursor, another 4 there.<br><br>That's a total of 1158 items to possibly track per character, and that doesn't account for flags, coin, crystals, task-journal, appearance settings, names, tribute, LDoN points, lockout timers, etc, and the framework to hold it all together.<br><br>To back up the entire game state (which is not just PC data but NPC timers and other game data) so that it can be rolled back to is probably easily nearing the range of terrabytes for all the servers combined. Which means a full backup alone of them is probably 2-3 hours alone.
