 space. Even if each record took up to 10 megs (which I doubt would be anywhere NEAR that large. I would say the record is probably less than 20k), I would stillestimate for each server the database would be under a terabyte, probably well under a terabyte for just character data per server. A chacter roll back wouldn't need the npc and other game data. It gets reset when the servers are taken down anway.</div><div></div><div>From what I have been told is that every item in your bank, every item on you, every stat you have is sent to the client each time you zone so how large can that really be?<br></div><div></div>
