<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=165217#M165217">14</a> of 23
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 623 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Easiest way to ensure fast, reliable backups that can be restored quickly is to use a RAID 1 mirror to store the data on.<br><br>So the process of patching/rollback would be trivial:<br><br><ol><li>bring down servers</li><li>break mirror</li><li>patch onto primary 1/2 of the now broken mirror</li><li>while patch is occuring do a full tape backup from the inactive, 2nd half of the broken mirror</li><li>bring up servers</li><li>if no problems after say 24 hours, re-stablish and re-sync the mirror</li><li>if rollback is needed:</li><li>take down servers.</li><li>bring up servers with the 2nd 1/2 of the mirror as primary disk (i.e. pre-patched set of files)</li><li>re-establish and re-sync the mirror (such that the 'patched' 1/2 is overwritten by the unpatched, original files)</li></ol>Much more reliable, and hugely faster than, relying on manual or even automatic backups by copying files (whether to tape or other disk).<br><div></div>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=159558">Eldakka 70 Ranger</a> of <a href="http://www.europaguild.net">Europa</a> Druzzil Ro<br><font color="red">"spellchecker? whats that? And why should I care?"</font><br>(70 Cleric, 70 Druid, 70 Enchanter)
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>01-19-2006</span> <span class=time_text>12:01 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
