<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=169465#M169465">17</a> of 23
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 408 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<div>Thinking more about the save/rollback mechanism, I've got a theory.</div><div></div><div>There are two types of character saves.</div><div></div><div><strong>1: Global Save</strong></div><div>This is done when servers are offline, and saves the entire server's character data in one shot. It provides a snapshot of the characters all at the same time</div><div></div><div><strong>2: Personal Save</strong></div><div>This is an ongoing 'rolling' process which happens while the servers are up. Characters are individually saved in the background while they're being played. There's no fixed time, characters are saved at different times from each other.</div><div></div><div>My guess is, they didn't have a recent enough Global Save, so had to rely on Personal Saves. Rolling back the entire character base to Personal Saves wasn't feasible, because they would all be at differing states. PlayerA hands PlayerB a sword.</div><ul><li>PlayerA was saved before the transaction, PlayerB was saved after it. Result: Both have the sword.</li><li>PlayerB was saved before the transaction, PlayerA was saved after it. Result: Sword no longer exists.</li></ul><div>This would have to happen for all 5 million characters in the database, and the duplication/deletion problems would be horrendous. If they're forced to use Personal Saves, inconveniencing 1% (according to SoE) is vastly preferable to subjecting 100%.</div><div></div><div>Obviously, the ideal situation would've been to rollback to a Global Save taken when the servers were down for the patch. If there <strong>wasn't</strong> a global save taken at that time, and the last Global Save was dated weeks ago, Personal Saves would be the only option, and targetting 'tainted' characters only would minimise the damage compared to just doing it to everyone.</div><div></div><div></div>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
