		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<div></div><p>ok let me say something it might be my work for the casinos here in the it department however, we use a program called zen-works to update all systems in a building or on our intranet a very simple and surprisingly short process system reboots on reboot the server recognizes the send from the client machine(The one being updated) And all data is backed up and then the new software or updates/changes are applied takes about 5-15 minutes to do. now SOE on the other hand makes a push and it takes 4 hours to do now where everyones thinking is flawed is that they believe that the developers make the changes. This is not the case the developers WRITE the programming code and package it the SYSTEM Administrators are the ones responsible for this and all other screw ups.</p><p>Now SOE claims that patching takes so long due to testing so either they are lieing flat out, OR have a bunch of idiots doing the testing how hard is it to see 25 mobs parked in one spot in POK???</p><p>Backing up should be done prior to any changes to live systems at the time of the changes again this boils down to incompitence and lazieness on the part of the system admins who arent doing their job.</p><p>Now I ask what the terrible harm would have been if SOE Had said &quot; OK So we screwed up and people saw the vendors and bought stuff ok lets jsut chalk that up to the person responsible fire them and leave it at that&quot; instead of punnishing the players for SOE System administrators mistakes.</p><p>I mean so what so people bought tradeskill items and madde things out of them if nothing else they should have realized this was an EXCELLENT REAL LIVE Test of the new recipies and items and cut their losses not subjected random people who werent even involved in the incident to the punishment that the system administrator responsible for being the moron who pushed the data to the live systems deserved!</p>	
